<br>
Your mother brought you into this world.  Before you say you didnt ask her to remember you can leave whenever you want.  Its obvious from your attitude that you don't believe in any moral accountability and therefor don't fear any responsibility after death.  I promise, world won't miss an attitude of ungreatfulness like yours.<br>
<br>
Not only did she bring you into this world but you are living in her house.  You say the time isn't right for you to move out?  Well then maybe the time is right to grow up so when you do move out you will be prepared.<br>
<br>
You not only have your own room, but you have a spare room used solely for storage.  I assume you have food or you would have stopped breathing a long time ago, and it seems like you have an abundance of hot air spewing from your mouth.<br>
<br>
95% of this world has grown up with a mother.  You want to bitch and whine about the few things she does wrong instead of be greatful for what she does right.  <br>
<br>
My mother and I disagreed.  We sometimes walked away mad.  I made the mistake of telling her I hated her once.  I was young, and we both knew I didn't mean it. One thing I NEVER did was talk bad about her to other people.  I respected her.  She deserved my respect.  I am guessing your mom does too.<br>
<br>
Even if your mother has NO redeeming qualities at all besides the fact that she keeps a roof over your head... that is enough for you to owe her some gratitude.<br>
<br>
Padlock your door when you leave, or don't leave stuff lying around, but don't get all whiney when your mom throws out your pot and porno mags.<br>
<br>
I don't know which is worse, the fact that you have this attitude, the fact that you publicly insulted your mother, or the fact that so few people have put you in your place for doing it.<br>
<br>
Oh, and you say you love her?  Forgive me for quoting some old cheesy Bon Jovi song... you give love a bad name.  Love goes hand in hand with respect, you don't love your mother, you love that she puts up with your crap and keeps you from having to grow up.<br>
<br>
Pankeleonn. Putting the "Whiney ass kid" in "EQ" <br>
