<br>
I'm sorry, but getting mad and repeatedly insulting your mother is totally different from sarcasm.  She has been feeding you, clothing you, keeping a roof over your lousy head all your life and this is how you treat her?  I'm sorry, but no amount of anger is an excuse for that.  I've been mad at my mother plenty of times.  When you live with someone for that long, you're going to argue once in awhile, but this goes way beyond that.  You will *never* be able to repay all that she's done for you and will continue to do for you (don't think that when you move out that you won't need your mother any more).  You should tell her thank you every time you fucking see her for all she's done, but all you can do is yell at her for something she may not have even done.  Ever thought of that?  No, of course not.  The majority of people living today can't take the blame for their own actions, why should you?<br>
<br>
If I were your mother, I would literally throw you out of the house, or find someone that could.  MAYBE you could take with you the things that YOU bought with money YOU earned from a job, but I'm guessing there aren't that many of those things laying around.  See how well you do without your mother, fucking bum.<br>
